siteV1AlarmNumber.name: siteV1AlarmNumber
siteV1AlarmNumber.description: The number of entries in the Site Alarm table

siteV1AlarmActive.description: Is the Alarm active ? 'true' for active, 'false' for not-active

siteV1AlarmSeverityType.description: The alarm severity type (major, minor, warning, none, disabled) of this alarm entry

siteV1AlarmSeverityLevel.description: The alarm severity level (0-9) of this alarm entry

siteV1AlarmStartTime.description: The last start time of this alarm entry (null if never active)

siteV1AlarmEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry - not used, only for MIB compliance

siteV1AlarmSummary.name: siteV1AlarmSummary
siteV1AlarmSummary.description: Summary bit vector with all the alarms state of the Site. A '1' means alarm active, '0' means not active. Unimplemented alarms are always '0'.

siteV1DataEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry - not used, only present for compliance

siteV1DataNetworkCurrentIPAddress.name: siteV1DataNetworkCurrentIPAddress
siteV1DataNetworkCurrentIPAddress.description: This is the actual IP address of the Comp@s platform. If the Ethernet cable is not correctly connected, the address will be 0.0.0.0.

siteV1DataNetworkCurrentIPMask.name: siteV1DataNetworkCurrentIPMask
siteV1DataNetworkCurrentIPMask.description: This is the actual IP address of the Comp@s platform. If the Ethernet cable is not correctly connected, the address will be 0.0.0.0.

siteV1DataNetworkCurrentMACAddress.name: siteV1DataNetworkCurrentMACAddress
siteV1DataNetworkCurrentMACAddress.description: This is the MAC address of IP interface.

siteV1DataControllerLicensedOptions.name: siteV1DataControllerLicensedOptions
siteV1DataControllerLicensedOptions.description: This is the options of the actual license.

siteV1DataTimeDateAndTimeLocal.name: siteV1DataTimeDateAndTimeLocal
siteV1DataTimeDateAndTimeLocal.description: This is the local time of the monitoring.

siteV1DataTimeDateAndTimeUTC.name: siteV1DataTimeDateAndTimeUTC
siteV1DataTimeDateAndTimeUTC.description: This is the UTC time of the monitoring.

siteV1DataControllerMonitoringMemoryUsed.name: siteV1DataControllerMonitoringMemoryUsed
siteV1DataControllerMonitoringMemoryUsed.description: This is actual amount of RAM memory used by the application.

siteV1DataControllerCPUPercentageUsage.name: siteV1DataControllerCPUPercentageUsage
siteV1DataControllerCPUPercentageUsage.description: This is actual percentage of CPU used

siteV1DataControllerFreeFlashMemorySpace.name: siteV1DataControllerFreeFlashMemorySpace
siteV1DataControllerFreeFlashMemorySpace.description: This is free flash memory available on the Comp@s card, in Megabytes

siteV1DataControllerFTPServerStatus.name: siteV1DataControllerFTPServerStatus
siteV1DataControllerFTPServerStatus.description: Status of the FTP Server. Compatible only with version >= 2.26.X.X. The configuration is available at controller -> FTP Server page.

siteV1DataInventoryCANBusNodeIDs.name: siteV1DataInventoryCANBusNodeIDs
siteV1DataInventoryCANBusNodeIDs.description: The coma separated list of the node ids present on the CAN bus.

siteV1ConfigNumber.name: siteV1ConfigNumber
siteV1ConfigNumber.description: The number of entries in the Config table related to the Site

siteV1ConfigTable.name: siteV1ConfigTable
siteV1ConfigTable.description: The table of Config entries related to the Site

siteV1ConfigEntryStatus.name: siteV1ConfigEntryStatus
siteV1ConfigEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry - not used, only for compliance

siteV1CfgNetworkDHCPEnabled.name: siteV1CfgNetworkDHCPEnabled
siteV1CfgNetworkDHCPEnabled.description: The monitoring will try to get an IP with the DHCP protocol if this parameter is set to True. By default, this parameter is set to False.

siteV1CfgNetworkIPAddressIfStatic.name: siteV1CfgNetworkIPAddressIfStatic
siteV1CfgNetworkIPAddressIfStatic.description: The static IP address of the monitoring. This configuration parameter is not used if the DHCP is enabled. The default IP is 192.168.45.2.

siteV1CfgNetworkSubnetMaskIfStatic.name: siteV1CfgNetworkSubnetMaskIfStatic
siteV1CfgNetworkSubnetMaskIfStatic.description: The static Subnet Mask of the monitoring. This configuration parameter is not used if the DHCP is enabled. The default mask is 255.255.255.0.

siteV1CfgNetworkDefaultGatewayIfStatic.name: siteV1CfgNetworkDefaultGatewayIfStatic
siteV1CfgNetworkDefaultGatewayIfStatic.description: The static Default Gateway of the monitoring. This configuration parameter is not used if DHCP is enabled. This is only useful if the monitoring have to use a gateway, this is generally not necessary. The default gateway is 192.168.45.1.

siteV1CfgNetworkDNSIfStatic.name: siteV1CfgNetworkDNSIfStatic
siteV1CfgNetworkDNSIfStatic.description: The static DNS of the monitoring. This configuration parameter is used to resolve URI and server name. This is not necessary if you are only IP address as target server. The default DNS server is 192.168.45.1.

siteV1CfgNetworkMaxTransmissionUnit.name: siteV1CfgNetworkMaxTransmissionUnit
siteV1CfgNetworkMaxTransmissionUnit.description: Specifies the TCP/IP MTU for the network interface

siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeServer.name: siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeServer
siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeServer.description: The address of the server acting as SNTP timer server. If this server is not valid, the monitoring cannot update automatically his time. You can use several time server by usin a coma separator without space.

siteV1CfgTimeTimeZoneName.name: siteV1CfgTimeTimeZoneName
siteV1CfgTimeTimeZoneName.description: The Time Zone of the site

siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeRefresh.name: siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeRefresh
siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeRefresh.description: Set the time between synchronisation with the SNTP server (max 1000 hours, by default 178)

siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeRecoveryRefresh.name: siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeRecoveryRefresh
siteV1CfgTimeSNTPTimeRecoveryRefresh.description: Set the time to wait before retry if a synchronisation fail (max 1000 hours, by default 24)

siteV1CfgWebServerWebServerSecurityEnabl.name: siteV1CfgWebServerWebServerSecurityEnabled
siteV1CfgWebServerWebServerSecurityEnabl.description: This is a True/False parameter used to activate or deactivate the access control to the web server.

siteV1CfgWebServerWebServerPort.name: siteV1CfgWebServerWebServerPort
siteV1CfgWebServerWebServerPort.description: This is an unsigned integer parameter used to configure the port at which the web server is accessible. By default, the port is 80. If you change this port, you must be sure that the traffic is allowed by your switches and routers on this port.

siteV1CfgWebServerWebAuthenticationMetho.name: siteV1CfgWebServerWebAuthenticationMethod
siteV1CfgWebServerWebAuthenticationMetho.description: The web access security can be managed with 3 authentication methods: Basic Access, Digest Access or Basic with Radius.

siteV1CfgWebServerHttpsWebServerPort.name: siteV1CfgWebServerHttpsWebServerPort
siteV1CfgWebServerHttpsWebServerPort.description: This is a port number to activate or deactivate the https web server - 0 or 443 by default

siteV1CfgWebServerDefaultPage.name: siteV1CfgWebServerDefaultPage
siteV1CfgWebServerDefaultPage.description: The default page displayed on logon (dashboard, site, summary, alarm_event, ...)

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingActivated.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingActivated
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingActivated.description: This is a True/False parameter used to activate or deactivate the XML event posting.

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingRefreshTime.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingRefreshTime
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingRefreshTime.description: The minimal time in second between to calculation of the XML events to send. By default, this is done every two seconds.

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingTimeout.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingTimeout
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingTimeout.description: The timeout in millisecond when trying to post XML data to a Web Server.

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingToSecOnlyIfPr.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingToSecOnlyIfPrimFail
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventPostingToSecOnlyIfPr.description: If this parameter is set to true, the events will be sent to secondary only if primary server is not available. If this parameter is set to false, all the events will be sent to primary and secondary server

siteV1CfgXMLXMLTablesToPostOnXMLEvent.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLTablesToPostOnXMLEvent
siteV1CfgXMLXMLTablesToPostOnXMLEvent.description: The list of the tables to send when an event is generated. (description,alarm,data,config,control). This allows to have armada database updated on event.

siteV1CfgXMLXMLHeartbeatTime.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLHeartbeatTime
siteV1CfgXMLXMLHeartbeatTime.description: This is the time between 2 XML Post of heartbeat. If set to 0, no heartbeat.

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPActivated.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPActivated
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPActivated.description: This is a True/False parameter used to activate or deactivate the SNMP agent.

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPTrapVersion.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPTrapVersion
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPTrapVersion.description: Traps/Notification can be sent with SNMP V1, V2c or V3 format.

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPGETMinSecurityLevel.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPGETMinSecurityLevel
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPGETMinSecurityLevel.description: 4 choices are available: No Authentication, V1 Community, V2c Community or V3.

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPSETMinSecurityLevel.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPSETMinSecurityLevel
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPSETMinSecurityLevel.description: 4 choices are available: No Authentication, V1 Community, V2c Community or V3.

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3AuthAlgorithm.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3AuthAlgorithm
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3AuthAlgorithm.description: 3 choices are available: MD5, SHA, Any

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3PrivacyPassword.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3PrivacyPassword
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3PrivacyPassword.description: The global SNMP V3 Encryption Password. This one is common for all the users to avoid complexity

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3EngineID.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3EngineID
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3EngineID.description: The SNMP V3 Local Engine ID string

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapUsername.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapUsername
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapUsername.description: The SNMP V3 Trap UserName used for all the SNMP V3 traps

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapAuthPassword.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapAuthPassword
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapAuthPassword.description: The SNMP V3 Trap Authentication Password

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapPrivacyPassword.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapPrivacyPassword
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPV3TrapPrivacyPassword.description: The SNMP V3 Trap Privacy Password

siteV1CfgSNMPSiteDescriptionIdsIncludedI.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSiteDescriptionIdsIncludedInTraps
siteV1CfgSNMPSiteDescriptionIdsIncludedI.description: List of site Description Elements to send on traps. (to have the site reference and the city in each trap for example). The list is separated with ';'

siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnConfChang.name: siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnConfChanges
siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnConfChang.description: This is a True/False parameter used to activate or deactivate the tracking of configuration changes

siteV1CfgDataRecordsAutoArchivePeriodDat.name: siteV1CfgDataRecordsAutoArchivePeriodDataRecord
siteV1CfgDataRecordsAutoArchivePeriodDat.description: Period in hour to auto save records (when detailled and long duration records are needed). 0 means disabled.

siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnControlEx.name: siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnControlExecution
siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnControlEx.description: This is a True/False parameter used to activate or deactivate the tracking of control execution

siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnAlarmAckn.name: siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnAlarmAcknowledge
siteV1CfgGenericGenerateEventOnAlarmAckn.description: This is a True/False parameter used to activate or deactivate the tracking of alarm acknowledgment

siteV1CfgInventoryRequiredCANBusNodeIDs.name: siteV1CfgInventoryRequiredCANBusNodeIDs
siteV1CfgInventoryRequiredCANBusNodeIDs.description: This is a coma separated list with the required CAN bus node ids

siteV1CfgInventoryLSSCANidrange.name: siteV1CfgInventoryLSSCANidrange
siteV1CfgInventoryLSSCANidrange.description: By default 50-80, means up to 50 Can Nodes like rectifiers with CAN Id 50 to 80. To support up to 100 rectifiers, change it to 1-100.

siteV1CfgUsersAdministratorLoginPassword.name: siteV1CfgUsersAdministratorLoginPassword
siteV1CfgUsersAdministratorLoginPassword.description: This is the login and the password of the administrator. It is saved with a special syntax. First the login in clear, followed of 2 points, followed of the MD5 hashed password. If you change the login:password by entering a non hashed password, this last is automatically hashed.

siteV1CfgUsersUser1LoginPassword.name: siteV1CfgUsersUser1LoginPassword
siteV1CfgUsersUser1LoginPassword.description: This is the login and the password of the user number 1.

siteV1CfgUsersUser2LoginPassword.name: siteV1CfgUsersUser2LoginPassword
siteV1CfgUsersUser2LoginPassword.description: This is the login and the password of the user number 2.

siteV1CfgUsersUser3LoginPassword.name: siteV1CfgUsersUser3LoginPassword
siteV1CfgUsersUser3LoginPassword.description: This is the login and the password of the user number 3.

siteV1CfgUsersUser4LoginPassword.name: siteV1CfgUsersUser4LoginPassword
siteV1CfgUsersUser4LoginPassword.description: This is the login and the password of the user number 4.

siteV1CfgUsersUser5LoginPassword.name: siteV1CfgUsersUser5LoginPassword
siteV1CfgUsersUser5LoginPassword.description: This is the login and the password of the user number 5.

siteV1CfgRadiusAuthenticationRadiusServe.name: siteV1CfgRadiusAuthenticationRadiusServer
siteV1CfgRadiusAuthenticationRadiusServe.description: Radius Server address. If you have a secondary server, you could use a coma to separate it.

siteV1CfgRadiusAuthenticationRadiusPort.name: siteV1CfgRadiusAuthenticationRadiusPort
siteV1CfgRadiusAuthenticationRadiusPort.description: Radius Port. If you have a secondary server, you could use a coma to separate it.

siteV1CfgEmailSmtpServer.name: siteV1CfgEmailSmtpServer
siteV1CfgEmailSmtpServer.description: Smtp Server. If you are using a domain name, make sure you configured the network Dns (CF5)

siteV1CfgEmailSmtpUserLoginPassword.name: siteV1CfgEmailSmtpUserLoginPassword
siteV1CfgEmailSmtpUserLoginPassword.description: Smtp Login and Password. The password is encrypted. To enter a new login and password, enter login:password and validate, the password will be encrypted.

siteV1CfgEmailMailSender.name: siteV1CfgEmailMailSender
siteV1CfgEmailMailSender.description: Mail Sender (The 'From' of the emails you will receive)

siteV1CfgEmailMinimalSeverityTypeToSendM.name: siteV1CfgEmailMinimalSeverityTypeToSendMail
siteV1CfgEmailMinimalSeverityTypeToSendM.description: This is the minimal severity of the event to send a Summary Mail

siteV1CfgControllerAutomaticReboot.name: siteV1CfgControllerAutomaticReboot
siteV1CfgControllerAutomaticReboot.description: Cron rules used in order to restart automatically the controller. Before rebooting configuration, events and data records are saved.

siteV1CfgCloudLinkCloudCredential.name: siteV1CfgCloudLinkCloudCredential
siteV1CfgCloudLinkCloudCredential.description: Enter Credential of your AlphaCloud account in order to connect. You have to enter username:password in order to save your credential.

siteV1CfgInventoryRS485ExtensionsConf.name: siteV1CfgInventoryRS485ExtensionsConf
siteV1CfgInventoryRS485ExtensionsConf.description: The configuration string for RS485 Extensions

siteV1CfgInventoryEthernetExtensionsConf.name: siteV1CfgInventoryEthernetExtensionsConf
siteV1CfgInventoryEthernetExtensionsConf.description: The configuration string for Ethernet Extensions

siteV1CfgScriptingEnabledscripts.name: siteV1CfgScriptingEnabledscripts
siteV1CfgScriptingEnabledscripts.description: This parameter enable all CompasLua Scripting capabilities. You can control scripts in Files -> Files manager > scripting tab.

siteV1CfgScriptingNumberofErrorsbeforetr.name: siteV1CfgScriptingNumberofErrorsbeforetriggeringalarm
siteV1CfgScriptingNumberofErrorsbeforetr.description: Number of errors before triggering the scripting error alarm. When number of error is higher than this parameter, the alarm is triggered. If 0 is set, the alarm is deactivated

siteV1CfgGenericReadAccessUserNumbers.name: siteV1CfgGenericReadAccessUserNumbers
siteV1CfgGenericReadAccessUserNumbers.description: The list of the user numbers which have read access to this equipment. The user numbers are coma separated. The accepted user id are 1,2,3,4 and 5. Ex: 1,3,4

siteV1CfgGenericWriteAccessUserNumbers.name: siteV1CfgGenericWriteAccessUserNumbers
siteV1CfgGenericWriteAccessUserNumbers.description: The list of the user numbers which have write access to this equipment. This means that these users can modify the configuration element, the alarm settings and use the control elements. The user numbers are coma separated. The accepted user ids are 1,2,3,4 and 5. Ex: 1,3,4

siteV1CfgGenericEventTableLength.name: siteV1CfgGenericEventTableLength
siteV1CfgGenericEventTableLength.description: The maximum length of the table. The value must be comprised between 10 and 4000

siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPTrapTargetsIP.name: siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPTrapTargetsIP
siteV1CfgSNMPSNMPTrapTargetsIP.description: One or multiple target IP to send traps, coma separated. Ex: 130.145.23.1, 130.23.12.45

siteV1CfgSNMPMinimalEventSeverityForTrap.name: siteV1CfgSNMPMinimalEventSeverityForTraps
siteV1CfgSNMPMinimalEventSeverityForTrap.description: This is the minimal severity of the event to send a SNMP trap

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostURL.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostURL
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostURL.description: This is the first URL at which the events related to this equipment must be posted. The XML ETSI standard is used in the posted data content.

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostLogin.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostLogin
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostLogin.description: The login which must be used when posting events to the primary server

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostPassword.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostPassword
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsPrimPostPassword.description: The password which must be used when posting events to the primary server

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostURL.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostURL
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostURL.description: This is the second URL at which the events related to this equipment must be posted. The XML ETSI standard is used in the posted data content. This allows having redundancy with the management server.

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostLogin.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostLogin
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostLogin.description: The login which must be used when posting events to the secondary server

siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostPassword.name: siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostPassword
siteV1CfgXMLXMLEventsSecPostPassword.description: The password which must be used when posting events to the secondary server

siteV1CfgPLCNumberOfPLCData.name: siteV1CfgPLCNumberOfPLCData
siteV1CfgPLCNumberOfPLCData.description: The number of PLC data. Every equipment can manage up to 30 user programmable data. Data elements are automatically added in the data table. Configuration parameters are added to set the PLC Data Name and the PLC Data Mathematical calculation. In order to use these functionalities, you need a license with the 'PLC' module

siteV1CfgPLCNumberOfPLCAlarm.name: siteV1CfgPLCNumberOfPLCAlarm
siteV1CfgPLCNumberOfPLCAlarm.description: The number of PLC alarm. Every equipment can manage up to 30 user programmable alarms. Alarm elements are automatically added in the alarm table. The alarm parameters are added to set the PLC Alarm Name and the PLC Alarm Boolean condition. In order to use these functionalities, you need a licence with the 'PLC' module

siteV1ControlNumber.name: siteV1ControlNumber
siteV1ControlNumber.description: The number of entries in the Control table related to the Site

siteV1ControlTable.name: siteV1ControlTable
siteV1ControlTable.description: The table of Control entries related to the Site

siteV1ControlEntryStatus.name: siteV1ControlEntryStatus
siteV1ControlEntryStatus.description: The status of this table entry - not used, only for compliance

siteV1CtrlControllerRebootController.name: siteV1CtrlControllerRebootController
siteV1CtrlControllerRebootController.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will reboot the monitoring. Events and Records will be saved.

siteV1CtrlControllerSaveConfAndRebootCon.name: siteV1CtrlControllerSaveConfAndRebootController
siteV1CtrlControllerSaveConfAndRebootCon.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will first save the actual configuration and will reboot the monitoring after.

siteV1CtrlControllerRebootControllerWith.name: siteV1CtrlControllerRebootControllerWithoutSavingRecords
siteV1CtrlControllerRebootControllerWith.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will reboot the monitoring without saving records

siteV1CtrlNetworkApplyNetworkConf.name: siteV1CtrlNetworkApplyNetworkConf
siteV1CtrlNetworkApplyNetworkConf.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will reconfigure the ethernet according to the Network Configuration. If you change the IP address in the config table without using this command after, the configuration is not applied.

siteV1CtrlTimeForceSNTPTimeRefresh.name: siteV1CtrlTimeForceSNTPTimeRefresh
siteV1CtrlTimeForceSNTPTimeRefresh.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will force the monitoring to try to refresh his time with the configured SNTP Time Server.

siteV1CtrlTimeSetLocalTime.name: siteV1CtrlTimeSetLocalTime
siteV1CtrlTimeSetLocalTime.description: Writing a date and time to this control element allows to manually change the local time of the monitoring. The syntax of the date and the time is: 2007-11-19T13:02:34

siteV1CtrlTimeSetUTCTime.name: siteV1CtrlTimeSetUTCTime
siteV1CtrlTimeSetUTCTime.description: Writing a date and time to this control element allows to manually change the UTC time of the monitoring. The syntax of the date and the time is: 2007-11-19T13:02:34

siteV1CtrlTimeResetUptime.name: siteV1CtrlTimeResetUptime
siteV1CtrlTimeResetUptime.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will reset the uptime of the monitoring.

siteV1CtrlControllerCleanandSaveXMLUserC.name: siteV1CtrlControllerCleanandSaveXMLUserConf
siteV1CtrlControllerCleanandSaveXMLUserC.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will remove the configuration sections related to missing equipments, than save all the configuration of all the connected equipment in a XML format. This file is read when the monitoring is starting in order to configure the monitoring. This file is also accessible trough the FTP server or can be downloaded trough the web interface.

siteV1CtrlControllerSaveXMLUserConf.name: siteV1CtrlControllerSaveXMLUserConf
siteV1CtrlControllerSaveXMLUserConf.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will save all the configuration of all the connected (or previously connected) equipment in a XML format. This file is read when the monitoring is starting in order to configure the monitoring. This file is also accessible trough the FTP server or can be downloaded trough the web interface.

siteV1CtrlControllerSaveInventory.name: siteV1CtrlControllerSaveInventory
siteV1CtrlControllerSaveInventory.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will save save the inventory in a XML format. This file is read when the monitoring is starting in order to configure the monitoring. This file is also accessible trough the FTP server or can be downloaded trough the web interface.

siteV1CtrlDataRecordsSaveDataRecords.name: siteV1CtrlDataRecordsSaveDataRecords
siteV1CtrlDataRecordsSaveDataRecords.description: Writing a '1' to this control element will force the monitoring to save all the data records. This is useful if you want to unpower the Comp@s monitoring. This function is called automatically everyday.

es1dc1CfgDCBusDCBusVoltageExtraHigh.description: The bus voltage over which the alarm 'DC Bus Voltage Extra High' is set.

es1dc1CfgDCBusDCBusVoltageExtraHighHyste.name: es1dc1CfgDCBusDCBusVoltageExtraHighHysteresis
es1dc1CfgDCBusDCBusVoltageExtraHighHyste.description: The voltage hysteresis on the alarm 'DC Bus Voltage Extra High

es1dc1CfgLVDLVDDisconnectVoltage.name: es1dc1CfgLVDLVDDisconnectVoltage
es1dc1CfgLVDLVDDisconnectVoltage.description: The dc bus voltage under which the battery must be disconnected of the bus. This allows preserving the battery life. The load will be unpowered. This value has to be lower than the Battery test end voltage (CF70)

es1dc1CfgLVDLVDDisconnectDelay.name: es1dc1CfgLVDLVDDisconnectDelay
es1dc1CfgLVDLVDDisconnectDelay.description: The delay in second before disconnecting the battery if the dc bus voltage is under the configured disconnected voltage. This avoids disconnection during a low bus transient.

es1dc1CfgBatTempCompensationSlope.name: es1dc1CfgBatTempCompensationSlope
es1dc1CfgBatTempCompensationSlope.description: The slope of the battery temperature compensation in mv/degree. For a 48V system, -72mV/degree is often used.

es1dc1CfgRectifiersMinimalNumberOfPresen.name: es1dc1CfgRectifiersMinimalNumberOfPresentRectifiers
es1dc1CfgRectifiersMinimalNumberOfPresen.description: The minimal number of rectifier which must be present. If there is less present rectifiers, the alarm 'Missing Rectifiers' is set.

es1dc1CfgRectifiersForcedRemoteOffRectif.name: es1dc1CfgRectifiersForcedRemoteOffRectifers
es1dc1CfgRectifiersForcedRemoteOffRectif.description: A list of rectifier which are forced in remote off. The id of the rectifier must be coma separated. Ex: 1,3 will maintain rectifier 1 and 3 off.

es1dc1CfgBatBatChargeCurrentLimit.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatChargeCurrentLimit
es1dc1CfgBatBatChargeCurrentLimit.description: The maximal battery current when the battery is charging. The monitoring regulates the bus voltage in order to satisfy this condition. This parameter is often equal to the nominal battery capacity divided by 10.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTempLow.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTempLow
es1dc1CfgBatBatTempLow.description: The temperature under which the alarm 'Battery Temperature Too Low' must be set.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTempHigh.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTempHigh
es1dc1CfgBatBatTempHigh.description: The temperature over which the alarm 'Battery Temperature Too High' must be set.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTempHysteresis.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTempHysteresis
es1dc1CfgBatBatTempHysteresis.description: The hysteresis on the 'Battery Temperature Too High' and 'Battery Temperature Too Low' alarms.

es1dc1CfgBatMinimalCurrentForDischarging.name: es1dc1CfgBatMinimalCurrentForDischargingAlarm
es1dc1CfgBatMinimalCurrentForDischarging.description: The minimal discharging current to set the 'Battery On Discharge' alarm.

es1dc1CfgBatCurrentHysteresisForDischarg.name: es1dc1CfgBatCurrentHysteresisForDischargingAlarm
es1dc1CfgBatCurrentHysteresisForDischarg.description: The hysteresis on the 'Battery On Discharge' alarm.

es1dc1CfgBatPeukertNumber.name: es1dc1CfgBatPeukertNumber
es1dc1CfgBatPeukertNumber.description: The Peukert number relates to the internal resistance of a battery and provides an indication of the excpected capacity. The ideal number is 1. This value can be calculated with the formula: (ln(t2)-ln(t1))/(ln(i1)-ln(i2)) where tx is the autonomy in hours at a constant discharge current of ix Amps. Often, we use t1 = 1h and t2 = 10h

es1dc1CfgBatMaxDepthOfDischargeforAutono.name: es1dc1CfgBatMaxDepthOfDischargeforAutonomyEstimation
es1dc1CfgBatMaxDepthOfDischargeforAutono.description: It is generally recommended to discharge maximum 60% of the battery capacity to enhance battery lifetime. By default, 100% is used for autonomy calculation. This parameter can also be used to take into account the age of the battery

es1dc1CfgBatBoostAutomatic.name: es1dc1CfgBatBoostAutomatic
es1dc1CfgBatBoostAutomatic.description: The boost mode must be automatically after the fact that during a mains failure, the bus voltage went under the configured 'Boost Activation Low Voltage'. This allows charging the battery faster.

es1dc1CfgBatBoostActivationLowVoltage.name: es1dc1CfgBatBoostActivationLowVoltage
es1dc1CfgBatBoostActivationLowVoltage.description: The voltage under which the boost mode can be activated.

es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationVoltage.name: es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationVoltage
es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationVoltage.description: The voltage over which the system must go back to floating mode.

es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationCurrent.name: es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationCurrent
es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationCurrent.description: The battery charging current under which the system must go back to floating mode.

es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationTime.name: es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationTime
es1dc1CfgBatBoostTerminationTime.description: The time in minute after which the system must go back in floating mode.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestType.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestType
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestType.description:
Type of the battery test:
Capacity based: The battery must give the requested capacity before falling lower than a value
Time Based: The battery must sustain a defined load during a defined time.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestEndVoltage.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestEndVoltage
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestEndVoltage.description: The voltage at which any battery test must be stopped. This value has to be higher than the LVD Disconnect voltage (CF10)

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDischargeRatio.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDischargeRatio
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDischargeRatio.description: The ratio of the battery capacity to discharge. If 30 is set, 30% of the battery will be discharged during the test

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestInterval.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestInterval
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestInterval.description: The number of days between two automatically started battery test. If this parameter is set to 0, the battery test is not started automatically. The user can remotely or locally start or force this test.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDischargeCurrent.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDischargeCurrent
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDischargeCurrent.description: The current at which the battery must be discharged during a battery test. The monitoring regulates the bus voltage in order to satisfy this condition. The load current must be of course higher than this parameter.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestMinimalDischargeCurre.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestMinimalDischargeCurrent
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestMinimalDischargeCurre.description: The battery current under which the battery test must be stopped because the load is too low.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDuration.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDuration
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestDuration.description: The timeout in minute after which the battery test must be stopped.

es1dc1CfgBatBatTestRequMinutesWithoutMai.name: es1dc1CfgBatBatTestRequMinutesWithoutMainsFail
es1dc1CfgBatBatTestRequMinutesWithoutMai.description: The minimal time in minute without mains failure in order to allow a battery start. This parameter is not taken into account when the battery test is forced.
